  Last night, a handful of Albion's held off a huge attack upon Hurbury. When the invasion firs started, I counted around 55 Hibs outside Hurbury.  When the Alb's finally made the retreat call (to the lord room) I counted 16 of us, only 2 of which were in plate. Most of the people were scouts, casters and clerics (since these were the people who didnt die outside the keep).  16 albs vs. 55 hibbies, we held them off the lord room for at least 25 minutes (though it seemed like forever) before reinforcements from merlin arrived.  The battle outside the lord room was very intense. See pics of the carnage at:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.petget.com/images/camelot/hurb1.gif">www.petget.com/images/camelot/hurb1.gif</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.petget.com/images/camelot/hurb2.gif">www.petget.com/images/camelot/hurb2.gif</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
(taken shortly after my own death). Hurbury was the 2nd to last keep left in Albion's hands, and the victory there turned the tide for the rest of the night. the Hurbury crew, and it's reinforcements, went on to take Sursbrooke and Beno back from the Hib/Mid forces.<br>
<br>
Despite the horrible lag, lousy frame rate, and hibbie pets pathing through the walls, I had a great time. It was one of those great battles you'll never forget (even after I said in the chat, when the Hibs were working on the 2nd keep door, &quot;Its like the Alamo here, you should probably stay at Merlin&quot;  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
