<br>
Not being that familiar with the location of the Lord's room I ran past it and up to the tower.  Healed like crazy on the steps until I went down (for some time).  Eventually we took back the stairway and I got a rez.  By this time my group of two (Rasha and I) were disbanded and I found myself solo.  What to do, what to do.<br>
<br>
I always wanted to know if I could effectively &quot;buff&quot; guards.  Soooo, I went up to the very top of the tower where I found two archers that had re-spawned.  I proceeded to give them the double dexterity buff and two shield buffs.  Unlike the problems I have had trying to &quot;defend&quot; behind tower walls (target not in view, etc. etc.)  Puter archers can effectively shoot thru walls.  Eventually, two other scouts showed up that I also buffed.  I can't confirm the amount of damage these archers did in total but it appeared they were firing arrows continuously.<br>
<br>
Great event - first time defending a keep.  My only complaint is I worked my ass off rezzing prolly 14 peeps, healing constantly to end up the evening with 0 realm points.  Seems us healer types should get something for helping out.<br>
<br>
